From: Andre Guedes <andre.guedes@openbossa.org>
Date: Tue, 24 Jul 2012 15:03:50 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 0301/1187] Bluetooth: Use lmp_rswitch_capable where
 applicable

commit 9f92ebf6c72de444801ab4a922965bd1f90834ae	upstream

This patch replaces all LMP_RSWITCH bit checking by the helper macro
lmp_rswitch_capable.

Signed-off-by: Andre Guedes <andre.guedes@openbossa.org>
Signed-off-by: Gustavo Padovan <gustavo.padovan@collabora.co.uk>
Signed-off-by: Lans Zhang <jia.zhang@windriver.com>
---
 net/bluetooth/hci_event.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/bluetooth/hci_event.c b/net/bluetooth/hci_event.c
index bbfa1d5..df97e81 100644
--- a/net/bluetooth/hci_event.c
+++ b/net/bluetooth/hci_event.c
@@ -623,7 +623,7 @@ static void hci_setup_link_policy(struct hci_dev *hdev)
 	struct hci_cp_write_def_link_policy cp;
 	u16 link_policy = 0;
 
-	if (hdev->features[0] & LMP_RSWITCH)
+	if (lmp_rswitch_capable(hdev))
 		link_policy |= HCI_LP_RSWITCH;
 	if (hdev->features[0] & LMP_HOLD)
 		link_policy |= HCI_LP_HOLD;
